  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p>\r\n<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 180&deg;C/ 160&deg;C (fan)/ 350&deg;F/ Gas 4</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the potatoes (with skin on) into 2cm pieces</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the potatoes and salt (optional) to a pot of boiling water and boil for 6 min or until you can just about pierce them with a knife</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, cut the leeks in half and wash to remove any grit from between the leaves</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the leeks into 2cm pieces for step 3</p>\r\n<p><strong>Crush</strong> the garlic with the back of a knife and chop (or grate) finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Drain</strong> the anchovy fillets of their oil and roughly chop</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> the potatoes are partially cooked, add the leeks to the same pot and boil for a further 4 min, or until both are tender</p>\r\n<p><strong>Drain</strong> well and transfer to a large mixing bowl</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> a saucepan over a low heat with 1 tbsp of olive oil and briefly fry the garlic and anchovies for 1 min until fragrant<br /><br /><strong>Add</strong> the cream and cook gently for 5 min, stirring occassionally</p>\r\n<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the cream mixture to the bowl of potato and leeks and gently mix to coat the vegetables</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> with pepper to your taste</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Turn</strong> the creamed potato and leek mixture into an ovenproof baking dish</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cover</strong> with foil and place in the oven for 30 min</p>\r\n<p><strong>After</strong> the 30 min, remove the foil, scatter the breadcrumbs over the surface, and bake for a further 8-10 min, or until lightly browned on top</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, finely chop the rosemary</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> into quarters </p>\r\n<p><strong>Mix</strong> together the rosemary, 3/4 of the lemon juice, 1-2 tbsp olive oil (extra virgin is best!) and season to taste with salt and pepper for your marinade</p>\r\n<p><strong>Trim</strong> any excess fat from the pork<br />Rub the marinade on both sides of the pork and set aside covered for 25-30 min</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> you've returned the potatoes to the oven for the final 8-10 min, begin cooking the pork</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a thick-based grill pan to a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, cook the pork for 4-5 min per side, or until cooked through</p>\r\n<p><strong>Remove</strong> from the heat and rest for 2 min</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve</strong> the pork with the potato and leek al forno and the remaining lemon on the side </p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
  ],
